### Description

When issuing an HTTP GET query with HttpClient, trailing whitespaces are stripped when there are no query parameters. However if there's at least one request param,the whitespace is properly encoded (%20)

Reproduction :
```
let params = new HttpParams();
this.http.get('/test ', {params}).subscribe( (res) => {
}, (err) => {
});
```
Observe in browser console; an HTTP request to '/test' is issued, stripping the white space

Add some parameter :
```
let params = new HttpParams();
params = params.set('hello', 'world');
this.http.get('/test ', {params}).subscribe( (res) => {
}, (err) => {
});
```
Request  issued is **/test%20?hello=world**


Expected behavior : stripping or encoding should be consistent if there are parameters or not


